WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.468 align:middle line:90%


00:00:01.468 --> 00:00:04.738 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:15.749 --> 00:00:16.416 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hi.

00:00:16.416 --> 00:00:17.317 align:middle line:90%
This is Lisa Garr.

00:00:17.317 --> 00:00:19.152 align:middle line:84%
And welcome to
"Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:19.152 --> 00:00:21.855 align:middle line:84%
We are coming to you live
from Boulder, Colorado.

00:00:21.855 --> 00:00:23.757 align:middle line:84%
And since this a live
show, we encourage

00:00:23.757 --> 00:00:26.226 align:middle line:84%
you to interact with us
on Facebook and Twitter.

00:00:26.226 --> 00:00:27.594 align:middle line:84%
Some of you have
already started,

00:00:27.594 --> 00:00:29.396 align:middle line:84%
so keep those
postings coming in.

00:00:29.396 --> 00:00:31.598 align:middle line:84%
We'll answer your questions
throughout the show.

00:00:31.598 --> 00:00:33.901 align:middle line:84%
So if you've ever been
one of those persons

00:00:33.901 --> 00:00:37.471 align:middle line:84%
who has received a phone call
about the passing of a loved

00:00:37.471 --> 00:00:40.707 align:middle line:84%
one, or if you've ever been
at the bedside of someone who

00:00:40.707 --> 00:00:43.844 align:middle line:84%
has passed over,
this show is for you.

00:00:43.844 --> 00:00:45.946 align:middle line:84%
And this is the
conversation that

00:00:45.946 --> 00:00:49.316 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Raymond Moody has
dedicated his life to,

00:00:49.316 --> 00:00:51.785 align:middle line:84%
is helping people
in this situation.

00:00:51.785 --> 00:00:55.255 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Moody is the author of a
book called "Life After Life,"

00:00:55.255 --> 00:00:57.791 align:middle line:90%
which is in its 37th year.

00:00:57.791 --> 00:01:00.193 align:middle line:84%
Millions of people
have read his book.

00:01:00.193 --> 00:01:03.063 align:middle line:84%
And he also has a new book
out called "Paranormal:

00:01:03.063 --> 00:01:05.299 align:middle line:84%
My Life in the Pursuit
of the Afterlife."

00:01:05.299 --> 00:01:07.334 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for
joining me, Dr. Moody.

00:01:07.334 --> 00:01:08.702 align:middle line:84%
>>RAYMOND MOODY:
Thank you, Lisa.

00:01:08.702 --> 00:01:10.003 align:middle line:90%
I'm just delighted to be here.

00:01:10.003 --> 00:01:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And thanks also to our
viewers who are watching.

00:01:13.140 --> 00:01:14.274 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, absolutely.

00:01:14.274 --> 00:01:16.076 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people are
very, very curious

00:01:16.076 --> 00:01:21.648 align:middle line:84%
about this concept of life after
death, near-death experiences.

00:01:21.648 --> 00:01:23.717 align:middle line:90%
Is there life after death?

00:01:23.717 --> 00:01:25.352 align:middle line:84%
How did you come
to write the book

00:01:25.352 --> 00:01:28.355 align:middle line:90%
37 years ago about this concept?

00:01:28.355 --> 00:01:30.123 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, I was
one of those kids who

00:01:30.123 --> 00:01:31.959 align:middle line:90%
just wasn't raised religious.

00:01:31.959 --> 00:01:34.661 align:middle line:84%
And when I went to the
University of Virginia

00:01:34.661 --> 00:01:37.997 align:middle line:84%
at the age of 18
to study astronomy,

00:01:37.997 --> 00:01:40.834 align:middle line:84%
actually-- but I'd been
interested in philosophy

00:01:40.834 --> 00:01:41.668 align:middle line:90%
in high school.

00:01:41.668 --> 00:01:46.773 align:middle line:84%
And literally in my first few
days as a first-year student

00:01:46.773 --> 00:01:50.077 align:middle line:84%
at the University
of Virginia in 1962,

00:01:50.077 --> 00:01:54.648 align:middle line:84%
reading Plato's "Republic" was
where I became aware of this.

00:01:54.648 --> 00:01:57.616 align:middle line:84%
Because Plato's
"Republic" is about

00:01:57.616 --> 00:01:59.786 align:middle line:84%
the question of
life after death.

00:01:59.786 --> 00:02:02.956 align:middle line:84%
And it culminates with
this amazing story

00:02:02.956 --> 00:02:05.492 align:middle line:84%
of a warrior who
was believed dead.

00:02:05.492 --> 00:02:08.996 align:middle line:84%
But during the funeral,
he spontaneously revived.

00:02:08.996 --> 00:02:10.530 align:middle line:90%
And he sat up.

00:02:10.530 --> 00:02:13.033 align:middle line:84%
And he talked to his friends
about leaving his body

00:02:13.033 --> 00:02:16.803 align:middle line:84%
and going through a passageway
into another world where

00:02:16.803 --> 00:02:19.373 align:middle line:90%
he saw his life reviewed.

00:02:19.373 --> 00:02:21.508 align:middle line:84%
And I was very impressed
with that story.

00:02:21.508 --> 00:02:25.412 align:middle line:84%
And I was absolutely
persuaded at age 18

00:02:25.412 --> 00:02:29.916 align:middle line:84%
by Plato's argument,
who said that this

00:02:29.916 --> 00:02:33.453 align:middle line:84%
is the most important
question of existence.

00:02:33.453 --> 00:02:36.656 align:middle line:84%
Then three years
later, still at UVA

00:02:36.656 --> 00:02:39.159 align:middle line:84%
as an undergraduate
philosophy student,

00:02:39.159 --> 00:02:42.696 align:middle line:84%
I heard about Dr. George
Ritchie, who was at that time

00:02:42.696 --> 00:02:46.266 align:middle line:84%
a professor of psychiatry at
the University of Virginia,

00:02:46.266 --> 00:02:50.137 align:middle line:84%
who some years before had had
this very experience in which

00:02:50.137 --> 00:02:53.406 align:middle line:84%
he had been pronounced
dead on two occasions, nine

00:02:53.406 --> 00:02:57.978 align:middle line:84%
minutes apart, and had this
phenomenal experience where--

00:02:57.978 --> 00:03:01.648 align:middle line:84%
listening to Doctor Ritchie
tell about this experience

00:03:01.648 --> 00:03:04.951 align:middle line:84%
was a life-changing
event in my life.

00:03:04.951 --> 00:03:08.155 align:middle line:84%
And to make a long story
short, since that time,

00:03:08.155 --> 00:03:10.390 align:middle line:84%
I've had the privilege,
as it really is,

00:03:10.390 --> 00:03:13.193 align:middle line:84%
of interviewing
literally thousands--

00:03:13.193 --> 00:03:16.063 align:middle line:84%
I'm not exaggerating--
thousands of people

00:03:16.063 --> 00:03:19.366 align:middle line:84%
from all over the world who
went to the brink of death

00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:22.069 align:middle line:84%
and who had this
amazing experience.

00:03:22.069 --> 00:03:24.304 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how does this
information, all these people

00:03:24.304 --> 00:03:27.207 align:middle line:84%
that you've interviewed
about near-death experiences,

00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:31.411 align:middle line:84%
how does that help the person
who has lost a loved one?

00:03:31.411 --> 00:03:33.914 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, doctors
all over the world

00:03:33.914 --> 00:03:36.116 align:middle line:84%
had studied these
near-death experiences.

00:03:36.116 --> 00:03:38.985 align:middle line:84%
And what we find
is that, for people

00:03:38.985 --> 00:03:41.288 align:middle line:84%
who haven't had
such an experience,

00:03:41.288 --> 00:03:44.024 align:middle line:84%
it really does seem to
be comforting to them

00:03:44.024 --> 00:03:50.497 align:middle line:84%
to hear these stories of people
who almost die and recover.

00:03:50.497 --> 00:03:53.767 align:middle line:84%
And also, I think
that for people

00:03:53.767 --> 00:03:57.037 align:middle line:84%
who are terminally ill,
that these stories are

00:03:57.037 --> 00:03:59.305 align:middle line:90%
very comforting.

00:03:59.305 --> 00:04:04.144 align:middle line:84%
Because generally what people
who almost die and recover

00:04:04.144 --> 00:04:07.280 align:middle line:84%
tell us was that, far from
being a bad experience,

00:04:07.280 --> 00:04:10.917 align:middle line:84%
it was in effect the
highlight of their life.

00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:13.553 align:middle line:84%
They say they enter into
an entirely different realm

00:04:13.553 --> 00:04:14.621 align:middle line:90%
of existence.

00:04:14.621 --> 00:04:15.422 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:04:15.422 --> 00:04:15.922 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:04:15.922 --> 00:04:19.059 align:middle line:84%
I have been through one
of these experiences

00:04:19.059 --> 00:04:23.263 align:middle line:84%
where I was in a severe
accident and left my body

00:04:23.263 --> 00:04:26.299 align:middle line:84%
and went up over the scene
and saw and felt and heard

00:04:26.299 --> 00:04:28.135 align:middle line:84%
all of the feelings of
the people below me,

00:04:28.135 --> 00:04:31.471 align:middle line:84%
and watched my body and
watched all the people.

00:04:31.471 --> 00:04:36.076 align:middle line:84%
It was the most extraordinary
experience I've ever had.

00:04:36.076 --> 00:04:39.513 align:middle line:84%
And I remember it
clearly, so clearly.

00:04:39.513 --> 00:04:41.114 align:middle line:90%
I was far from unconscious.

00:04:41.114 --> 00:04:44.217 align:middle line:84%
I was more conscious
than I ever, ever was.

00:04:44.217 --> 00:04:46.253 align:middle line:84%
It was an expanded
consciousness.

00:04:46.253 --> 00:04:46.786 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:04:46.786 --> 00:04:47.687 align:middle line:90%
Exactly right.

00:04:47.687 --> 00:04:50.223 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we're going
to go through today some

00:04:50.223 --> 00:04:52.792 align:middle line:84%
of the classic characteristics
that Dr. Moody has

00:04:52.792 --> 00:04:55.395 align:middle line:84%
so eloquently put into
place for people like me

00:04:55.395 --> 00:04:57.998 align:middle line:84%
and anyone else who's had
an experience like this,

00:04:57.998 --> 00:05:00.834 align:middle line:84%
to be able to identify
with that experience that

00:05:00.834 --> 00:05:05.772 align:middle line:84%
was so mysterious to me
that I had no words for it--

00:05:05.772 --> 00:05:07.474 align:middle line:84%
I still struggle
to find words for--

00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:09.509 align:middle line:84%
and that's actually one
of the characteristics.

00:05:09.509 --> 00:05:11.511 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to go
through these in detail.

00:05:11.511 --> 00:05:13.346 align:middle line:84%
So if you've ever
been though this,

00:05:13.346 --> 00:05:15.248 align:middle line:84%
you have a way to
identify with this.

00:05:15.248 --> 00:05:16.983 align:middle line:84%
And also, if you
haven't been through it,

00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:19.686 align:middle line:84%
you understand a little
bit more about what

00:05:19.686 --> 00:05:24.357 align:middle line:84%
happens to people who go through
this, quote, tunnel of death.

00:05:24.357 --> 00:05:29.796 align:middle line:84%
We have a clip to show you that
kind of encapsulates what--

00:05:29.796 --> 00:05:31.965 align:middle line:84%
from a movie called
"Life After Life" that

00:05:31.965 --> 00:05:34.367 align:middle line:84%
was made after Dr.
Raymond Moody's book.

00:05:34.367 --> 00:05:37.437 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at that.

00:05:37.437 --> 00:05:38.805 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:05:38.805 --> 00:05:41.374 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:48.715 --> 00:05:51.985 align:middle line:84%
>>The lightning came down the
phone line, entered my neck.

00:05:51.985 --> 00:05:55.555 align:middle line:84%
It went through my spine,
threw me up in air.

00:05:55.555 --> 00:05:58.525 align:middle line:84%
>>And I felt myself
pop out of the body.

00:05:58.525 --> 00:06:01.761 align:middle line:84%
Then I felt myself
float up to the ceiling.

00:06:01.761 --> 00:06:04.197 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor and the
nurse were in there.

00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:05.398 align:middle line:90%
And he was looking at me.

00:06:05.398 --> 00:06:06.866 align:middle line:90%
Said, "She's gone.

00:06:06.866 --> 00:06:08.201 align:middle line:90%
She's dead."

00:06:08.201 --> 00:06:11.738 align:middle line:90%
>>And I was taken to hospital.

00:06:11.738 --> 00:06:15.742 align:middle line:84%
Doctors did anything
they could to help me,

00:06:15.742 --> 00:06:19.746 align:middle line:90%
but I was declared dead.

00:06:19.746 --> 00:06:21.915 align:middle line:84%
>>I realized I
was out of my body

00:06:21.915 --> 00:06:25.485 align:middle line:84%
when I was suddenly
looking at this light.

00:06:25.485 --> 00:06:27.821 align:middle line:84%
>>Out of that stepped
the most amazing being

00:06:27.821 --> 00:06:29.456 align:middle line:84%
I have ever been
in the presence of.

00:06:29.456 --> 00:06:35.962 align:middle line:84%
>>It was just all-consuming
love, wonderful love.

00:06:35.962 --> 00:06:38.965 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:14.901 --> 00:07:16.836 align:middle line:84%
>>Death is nothing more
or less than a doorway,

00:07:16.836 --> 00:07:18.705 align:middle line:90%
something you walk through.

00:07:18.705 --> 00:07:20.674 align:middle line:84%
>>(ECHOING) Death
does not exist.

00:07:20.674 --> 00:07:21.474 align:middle line:90%
Don't be afraid.

00:07:45.665 --> 00:07:50.470 align:middle line:84%
>>This was holographical view
of being inside of your life

00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:54.707 align:middle line:84%
and then being as a
viewer, participating

00:07:54.707 --> 00:07:56.176 align:middle line:90%
the play of theater.

00:08:14.461 --> 00:08:17.997 align:middle line:84%
>>He was asking me had I learned
to love my fellow human beings

00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:21.000 align:middle line:84%
the way that he totally
accepted and loved me.

00:08:47.260 --> 00:08:48.328 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:08:48.328 --> 00:08:50.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how many
people have come to you

00:08:50.530 --> 00:08:51.865 align:middle line:90%
since you've written the book?

00:08:51.865 --> 00:08:54.033 align:middle line:84%
How many thousands of
people have come to you

00:08:54.033 --> 00:08:55.802 align:middle line:90%
with these experiences?

00:08:55.802 --> 00:08:57.570 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: You know,
Lisa, literally, I

00:08:57.570 --> 00:08:58.838 align:middle line:90%
have no way of tracking it.

00:08:58.838 --> 00:09:02.642 align:middle line:84%
This is something I hear
numerous times a week.

00:09:02.642 --> 00:09:03.276 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A week.

00:09:03.276 --> 00:09:03.777 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:09:03.777 --> 00:09:04.477 align:middle line:90%
>>Yeah.

00:09:04.477 --> 00:09:07.914 align:middle line:84%
And literally thousands
of people since I

00:09:07.914 --> 00:09:11.117 align:middle line:84%
first heard Dr.
Ritchie speak in 1965.

00:09:11.117 --> 00:09:12.352 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That have come to you.

00:09:12.352 --> 00:09:13.787 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't even come to you.

00:09:13.787 --> 00:09:17.190 align:middle line:84%
I saw the-- you have a whole
posting on the internet

00:09:17.190 --> 00:09:19.426 align:middle line:84%
through your Life
After Life website.

00:09:19.426 --> 00:09:21.060 align:middle line:84%
And it shows the
characteristics,

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:22.629 align:middle line:84%
which we're going
to go through today.

00:09:22.629 --> 00:09:26.733 align:middle line:84%
But it was so healing for me to
identify with that and to see--

00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:28.701 align:middle line:84%
And I wound up
taking your course

00:09:28.701 --> 00:09:29.869 align:middle line:90%
through my master's program.

00:09:29.869 --> 00:09:31.638 align:middle line:84%
And it was very,
very enlightening.

00:09:31.638 --> 00:09:34.207 align:middle line:84%
So let's go through some
of the characteristics.

00:09:34.207 --> 00:09:34.741 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:36.209 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is
the typical, like--

00:09:36.209 --> 00:09:37.343 align:middle line:90%
this is general, of course.

00:09:37.343 --> 00:09:39.012 align:middle line:84%
This isn't the same
for everyone, right?

00:09:39.012 --> 00:09:40.380 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: That's right.

00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:44.484 align:middle line:84%
People go into this
more deeply the longer

00:09:44.484 --> 00:09:46.419 align:middle line:90%
they're close to death.

00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:49.889 align:middle line:84%
So that someone who has
an extended cardiac arrest

00:09:49.889 --> 00:09:52.859 align:middle line:84%
is more likely to tell
you this whole picture.

00:09:52.859 --> 00:09:56.830 align:middle line:84%
Whereas somebody, for example,
with only momentary cardiac

00:09:56.830 --> 00:09:59.833 align:middle line:84%
arrest will just tell you one
or two or three of these things.

00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:03.536 align:middle line:84%
But in the typical case
we've seen many times,

00:10:03.536 --> 00:10:06.639 align:middle line:84%
people will tell us that at this
point where their heart stops

00:10:06.639 --> 00:10:09.843 align:middle line:84%
beating, they actually
hear their doctor say,

00:10:09.843 --> 00:10:12.979 align:middle line:84%
oh my god, he's dead,
or words to that effect.

00:10:12.979 --> 00:10:15.215 align:middle line:84%
Which comes as a big
surprise to them,

00:10:15.215 --> 00:10:18.618 align:middle line:84%
because they say, as you
did, that paradoxically, I've

00:10:18.618 --> 00:10:20.820 align:middle line:84%
heard people say,
I've never felt

00:10:20.820 --> 00:10:24.457 align:middle line:84%
so alive as when I heard
my doctor say I was dead.

00:10:24.457 --> 00:10:25.592 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You can't say it.

00:10:25.592 --> 00:10:26.226 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:10:26.226 --> 00:10:28.995 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: And people
say that they rise up.

00:10:28.995 --> 00:10:31.965 align:middle line:84%
They see their own
physical bodies down below.

00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:34.067 align:middle line:84%
They watch as the
doctors and nurses

00:10:34.067 --> 00:10:36.336 align:middle line:90%
are trying to resuscitate them.

00:10:36.336 --> 00:10:39.706 align:middle line:84%
But after a while on this,
it kind of dawns on them, oh,

00:10:39.706 --> 00:10:42.642 align:middle line:84%
that since I'm out of my
body, nobody can see me.

00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:43.643 align:middle line:90%
I try to talk.

00:10:43.643 --> 00:10:45.044 align:middle line:90%
Nobody can hear me.

00:10:45.044 --> 00:10:46.513 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's a
sense of surrender.

00:10:46.513 --> 00:10:47.046 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:10:47.046 --> 00:10:47.814 align:middle line:90%
Surrender.

00:10:47.814 --> 00:10:50.116 align:middle line:84%
And at this point,
they tell us they

00:10:50.116 --> 00:10:52.118 align:middle line:84%
enter into states
of consciousness

00:10:52.118 --> 00:10:55.388 align:middle line:84%
that, no matter how
articulate they may be

00:10:55.388 --> 00:10:58.658 align:middle line:84%
or how many languages
they may speak, they say

00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:01.828 align:middle line:84%
they simply have no
words to describe this,

00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:04.464 align:middle line:90%
that it lies beyond words.

00:11:04.464 --> 00:11:06.032 align:middle line:84%
But the way they
try to describe it,

00:11:06.032 --> 00:11:09.536 align:middle line:84%
they say they go through
a passageway, which

00:11:09.536 --> 00:11:12.605 align:middle line:84%
they may compare to
a tunnel or a tube.

00:11:12.605 --> 00:11:14.874 align:middle line:84%
And they say they come
out on the other side

00:11:14.874 --> 00:11:20.680 align:middle line:84%
of this passageway in an
incredibly brilliant light,

00:11:20.680 --> 00:11:24.317 align:middle line:84%
far brighter than anything that
we have seen while we're alive.

00:11:24.317 --> 00:11:25.852 align:middle line:90%
But it's not uncomfortable.

00:11:25.852 --> 00:11:28.254 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of
fact, the reverse.

00:11:28.254 --> 00:11:32.992 align:middle line:84%
They feel completely
comforted, at peace, joyful,

00:11:32.992 --> 00:11:37.764 align:middle line:84%
and pervaded by this amazing
love, far beyond the love

00:11:37.764 --> 00:11:40.500 align:middle line:90%
that we feel while we're here.

00:11:40.500 --> 00:11:45.004 align:middle line:84%
And in that light, they tell
us that relatives or friends

00:11:45.004 --> 00:11:47.173 align:middle line:84%
of theirs who have
already died seem

00:11:47.173 --> 00:11:49.175 align:middle line:84%
to be there almost as
a greeting committee,

00:11:49.175 --> 00:11:50.710 align:middle line:84%
to help them through
this transition.

00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:51.978 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: In a peaceful way.

00:11:51.978 --> 00:11:52.545 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:56.182 align:middle line:84%
And they-- at some point
this whole environment kind

00:11:56.182 --> 00:11:59.886 align:middle line:84%
of disappears, and they
find themselves surrounded

00:11:59.886 --> 00:12:05.258 align:middle line:84%
by a full-color,
three-dimensional, holographic

00:12:05.258 --> 00:12:10.029 align:middle line:84%
panorama consisting in many
cases of every single thing

00:12:10.029 --> 00:12:10.763 align:middle line:90%
they've ever done.

00:12:10.763 --> 00:12:12.065 align:middle line:84%
It's right there
displayed before them.

00:12:12.065 --> 00:12:13.132 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:12:13.132 --> 00:12:16.002 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: And they say that
even though-- because language

00:12:16.002 --> 00:12:18.738 align:middle line:84%
is sequential-- that
when they tell this,

00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:21.874 align:middle line:84%
they have to tell it as
though it were a sequence.

00:12:21.874 --> 00:12:25.211 align:middle line:84%
That in the experiencing
of it, literally everything

00:12:25.211 --> 00:12:26.212 align:middle line:90%
is there at once.

00:12:26.212 --> 00:12:26.813 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:27.914 align:middle line:90%
It's non-linear.

00:12:27.914 --> 00:12:28.448 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yep.

00:12:28.448 --> 00:12:32.051 align:middle line:84%
And they say that in
this panorama, when

00:12:32.051 --> 00:12:34.954 align:middle line:84%
you see yourself
doing an action,

00:12:34.954 --> 00:12:39.659 align:middle line:84%
that you see yourself as
though you're another person.

00:12:39.659 --> 00:12:44.163 align:middle line:84%
But when that action has its
impact or its consequences,

00:12:44.163 --> 00:12:46.199 align:middle line:84%
you are embedded in
the consciousness

00:12:46.199 --> 00:12:48.635 align:middle line:84%
of those with whom
you've interacted.

00:12:48.635 --> 00:12:51.070 align:middle line:84%
And hence, if you see
yourself doing something

00:12:51.070 --> 00:12:53.606 align:middle line:84%
mean to somebody,
then in this review

00:12:53.606 --> 00:12:57.276 align:middle line:84%
you feel empathically
and directly the hurt

00:12:57.276 --> 00:12:59.579 align:middle line:84%
that you brought about
in that person's life.

00:12:59.579 --> 00:13:02.415 align:middle line:84%
Or if you see yourself
doing something loving,

00:13:02.415 --> 00:13:03.816 align:middle line:90%
then you feel the good feelings.

00:13:03.816 --> 00:13:04.517 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:13:04.517 --> 00:13:06.252 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: At a certain
point, obviously,

00:13:06.252 --> 00:13:07.654 align:middle line:90%
people have to come back.

00:13:07.654 --> 00:13:10.390 align:middle line:84%
Some people say they have
no idea how they got back.

00:13:10.390 --> 00:13:12.125 align:middle line:84%
Just one moment they
were in this light,

00:13:12.125 --> 00:13:15.161 align:middle line:84%
then they were back on
the ER table or whatever.

00:13:15.161 --> 00:13:17.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The movie-- the
"Life After Life" movie

00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.464 align:middle line:84%
does a really good
job of showing

00:13:18.464 --> 00:13:20.667 align:middle line:84%
some interviews of people
who have been through this.

00:13:20.667 --> 00:13:22.669 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at that.

00:13:22.669 --> 00:13:26.839 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:13:26.839 --> 00:13:28.207 align:middle line:84%
>>Pretty much all
over the world,

00:13:28.207 --> 00:13:31.511 align:middle line:90%
we found this common pattern.

00:13:31.511 --> 00:13:34.814 align:middle line:84%
They tell us that at this
point where their doctor says

00:13:34.814 --> 00:13:37.684 align:middle line:84%
they are dead, that
they may actually

00:13:37.684 --> 00:13:41.187 align:middle line:84%
hear the physician
say, oh my, he's dead,

00:13:41.187 --> 00:13:44.057 align:middle line:84%
or we've lost her, or
something like that.

00:13:44.057 --> 00:13:46.225 align:middle line:84%
And they say that from
their perspective, actually,

00:13:46.225 --> 00:13:48.061 align:middle line:90%
they still feel very much alive.

00:13:48.061 --> 00:13:50.797 align:middle line:84%
Indeed their consciousness
is heightened.

00:13:50.797 --> 00:13:54.400 align:middle line:84%
And they tell us that they seem
to leave their physical bodies.

00:13:54.400 --> 00:13:57.070 align:middle line:84%
They say that they
float up, typically

00:13:57.070 --> 00:14:01.074 align:middle line:84%
right above the bed in the
operating room or the emergency

00:14:01.074 --> 00:14:01.574 align:middle line:90%
room.

00:14:01.574 --> 00:14:02.742 align:middle line:90%
And they look down.

00:14:02.742 --> 00:14:05.344 align:middle line:84%
And they can see their
own physical bodies

00:14:05.344 --> 00:14:07.013 align:middle line:90%
lying on the bed down below.

00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:08.114 align:middle line:90%
>>I was above my body.

00:14:08.114 --> 00:14:09.115 align:middle line:90%
I was floating.

00:14:09.115 --> 00:14:10.583 align:middle line:90%
And there were people around me.

00:14:10.583 --> 00:14:14.487 align:middle line:84%
Except I didn't realize that
that person there was me.

00:14:14.487 --> 00:14:15.321 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:14:15.321 --> 00:14:16.956 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So Heather
from Facebook is

00:14:16.956 --> 00:14:19.459 align:middle line:84%
asking-- what's the difference
between when you leave

00:14:19.459 --> 00:14:23.062 align:middle line:84%
your body and when you're
just projecting or floating

00:14:23.062 --> 00:14:24.597 align:middle line:84%
above your body in
like a meditation?

00:14:24.597 --> 00:14:26.032 align:middle line:90%
What's the difference there?

00:14:26.032 --> 00:14:28.034 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, that's a
great question, Heather.

00:14:28.034 --> 00:14:32.905 align:middle line:84%
And what we have here is
a continuum or a spectrum

00:14:32.905 --> 00:14:35.308 align:middle line:84%
rather than a
discrete difference.

00:14:35.308 --> 00:14:37.376 align:middle line:84%
And the experience
you're describing

00:14:37.376 --> 00:14:41.047 align:middle line:84%
there of leaving the body
occurs, as you're intimating,

00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:45.618 align:middle line:84%
not just in the case of somebody
who almost dies and recovers,

00:14:45.618 --> 00:14:47.253 align:middle line:90%
but other cases as well.

00:14:47.253 --> 00:14:50.490 align:middle line:84%
For example, you mentioned
the meditative state.

00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:53.693 align:middle line:84%
And also the out-of-body
experiences sometimes

00:14:53.693 --> 00:14:57.230 align:middle line:84%
occur to music performers
while they're on stage.

00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:58.698 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, so
there's a difference

00:14:58.698 --> 00:15:01.601 align:middle line:84%
between a near-death experience
and an out-of-body experience.

00:15:01.601 --> 00:15:02.769 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Well, I think, yes.

00:15:02.769 --> 00:15:05.338 align:middle line:84%
The out-of-body
experience is something

00:15:05.338 --> 00:15:09.108 align:middle line:84%
that occurs sometimes in
a near-death experience

00:15:09.108 --> 00:15:12.512 align:middle line:84%
and sometimes in other cases,
like performing great music.

00:15:12.512 --> 00:15:16.749 align:middle line:84%
Or astronomers occasionally
gazing through their telescopes

00:15:16.749 --> 00:15:18.951 align:middle line:84%
will have out-of-body
experiences.

00:15:18.951 --> 00:15:22.555 align:middle line:84%
And so it occurs
not just in the case

00:15:22.555 --> 00:15:25.925 align:middle line:84%
of a near-death experience,
but also in these other cases.

00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:28.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now, can
these experiences

00:15:28.060 --> 00:15:31.764 align:middle line:84%
be replicated in any kind--
type of controlled situation,

00:15:31.764 --> 00:15:35.134 align:middle line:90%
a near-death experience?

00:15:35.134 --> 00:15:37.737 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, I
think parts of it can.

00:15:37.737 --> 00:15:42.175 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that the entire
near-death experience can

00:15:42.175 --> 00:15:45.344 align:middle line:84%
be replicated yet,
but parts of it.

00:15:45.344 --> 00:15:48.781 align:middle line:84%
And there are different
ways, for example,

00:15:48.781 --> 00:15:51.384 align:middle line:84%
of inducing an
out-of-body state.

00:15:51.384 --> 00:15:55.388 align:middle line:84%
And another
circumstance in which

00:15:55.388 --> 00:16:00.293 align:middle line:84%
people without almost dying
can have these experiences

00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:03.429 align:middle line:84%
is at the bedside of
someone who does die.

00:16:03.429 --> 00:16:07.567 align:middle line:84%
It's very common, for
example, when somebody dies,

00:16:07.567 --> 00:16:10.837 align:middle line:84%
and the loved ones are standing
around as the person in the bed

00:16:10.837 --> 00:16:14.907 align:middle line:84%
dies, the bystanders themselves
may have all of these features

00:16:14.907 --> 00:16:17.476 align:middle line:84%
that we talk about as a
near-death experience,

00:16:17.476 --> 00:16:20.947 align:middle line:84%
including seeing the spirit
of the departing person

00:16:20.947 --> 00:16:22.281 align:middle line:90%
leave the body.

00:16:22.281 --> 00:16:26.619 align:middle line:84%
Or in many cases, the bystanders
will say that they themselves

00:16:26.619 --> 00:16:28.588 align:middle line:84%
feel they leave
their physical bodies

00:16:28.588 --> 00:16:32.625 align:middle line:84%
and accompany their dying loved
one part way toward this light.

00:16:32.625 --> 00:16:35.228 align:middle line:84%
Or the bystanders may
see the room fill up

00:16:35.228 --> 00:16:36.562 align:middle line:90%
with this beautiful light.

00:16:36.562 --> 00:16:39.565 align:middle line:90%
Or they may hear gorgeous music.

00:16:39.565 --> 00:16:42.735 align:middle line:84%
Or they say sometimes
that they perceive

00:16:42.735 --> 00:16:45.805 align:middle line:84%
the spirits of the
deceased person-- I

00:16:45.805 --> 00:16:50.776 align:middle line:84%
mean the spirits of
the deceased relatives

00:16:50.776 --> 00:16:53.613 align:middle line:90%
and friends of the dying person.

00:16:53.613 --> 00:16:57.750 align:middle line:84%
And I've had cases in which the
bystander actually empathically

00:16:57.750 --> 00:17:02.121 align:middle line:84%
co-lives the panoramic life
review of the person who

00:17:02.121 --> 00:17:02.688 align:middle line:90%
passes away.

00:17:02.688 --> 00:17:04.723 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what a
shared death experience is?

00:17:04.723 --> 00:17:05.523 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Shared
death experience.

00:17:05.523 --> 00:17:05.657 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fascinating.

00:17:05.657 --> 00:17:08.127 align:middle line:84%
There's actually a really good
part in the movie about that.

00:17:08.127 --> 00:17:10.262 align:middle line:84%
This is the Gaiam movie
"Life After Life."

00:17:10.262 --> 00:17:13.132 align:middle line:90%
Take a look at this.

00:17:13.132 --> 00:17:16.068 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:17:16.068 --> 00:17:19.070 align:middle line:84%
>>There's a skeptical
part of me, too.

00:17:19.070 --> 00:17:22.275 align:middle line:84%
And I wonder sometimes
whether or not

00:17:22.275 --> 00:17:25.778 align:middle line:84%
this might just be
people's hallucinations

00:17:25.778 --> 00:17:29.348 align:middle line:84%
that they're going
through, or just

00:17:29.348 --> 00:17:34.520 align:middle line:84%
a natural shutting-down process
when the brain is dying.

00:17:34.520 --> 00:17:37.957 align:middle line:84%
>>I used to wonder about
that myself, Peter.

00:17:37.957 --> 00:17:41.360 align:middle line:84%
What has turned me around on
that issue is that so often

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:43.663 align:middle line:84%
these patients are
able to give us

00:17:43.663 --> 00:17:46.465 align:middle line:84%
very correct descriptions
of what was going on

00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:49.235 align:middle line:84%
during the resuscitation
from a point of view

00:17:49.235 --> 00:17:51.871 align:middle line:84%
they couldn't have had
from that perspective

00:17:51.871 --> 00:17:55.942 align:middle line:84%
of that physical body
lying on the table.

00:17:55.942 --> 00:18:00.346 align:middle line:84%
For instance, my friend Kim, who
works at a medical university

00:18:00.346 --> 00:18:02.982 align:middle line:84%
out west, was
telling me that she

00:18:02.982 --> 00:18:08.621 align:middle line:84%
was involved in resuscitating
a young patient named Maria.

00:18:08.621 --> 00:18:12.725 align:middle line:84%
And Maria had been believed dead
but was successfully revived.

00:18:12.725 --> 00:18:15.895 align:middle line:84%
And when she came
back to consciousness,

00:18:15.895 --> 00:18:21.434 align:middle line:84%
my friend Kim happened to be
standing there by her bedside.

00:18:21.434 --> 00:18:26.639 align:middle line:84%
And Maria grabbed onto Kim and
said during the resuscitation,

00:18:26.639 --> 00:18:28.874 align:middle line:84%
when she was out
of her body, she

00:18:28.874 --> 00:18:32.311 align:middle line:84%
drifted outside of the hospital
entirely and saw an old shoe

00:18:32.311 --> 00:18:37.249 align:middle line:84%
on a ledge on a window outside
an upper floor of the hospital.

00:18:37.249 --> 00:18:39.418 align:middle line:84%
And Kim was actually
able to go there

00:18:39.418 --> 00:18:42.955 align:middle line:84%
and to verify that
the shoe was there

00:18:42.955 --> 00:18:46.192 align:middle line:84%
exactly as the
patient had specified.

00:18:46.192 --> 00:18:47.994 align:middle line:90%
>>Really.

00:18:47.994 --> 00:18:51.697 align:middle line:84%
>>And all of a sudden, aware
of people out in the hall.

00:18:51.697 --> 00:18:53.799 align:middle line:84%
The room had been
sealed off because he

00:18:53.799 --> 00:18:57.737 align:middle line:84%
was going to do
surgery in the room.

00:18:57.737 --> 00:19:02.074 align:middle line:84%
So I immediately went
out through the door.

00:19:02.074 --> 00:19:03.776 align:middle line:90%
Did not open it, just went out.

00:19:03.776 --> 00:19:07.613 align:middle line:84%
I was immediately on the
other side of it, in the hall.

00:19:07.613 --> 00:19:10.383 align:middle line:90%
But I go up to my daughter.

00:19:10.383 --> 00:19:13.919 align:middle line:84%
And I try to make her hear
me, "Kathy, go home and change

00:19:13.919 --> 00:19:15.154 align:middle line:90%
your clothes."

00:19:15.154 --> 00:19:18.624 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't make her hear
me, so I went to her dad.

00:19:18.624 --> 00:19:20.292 align:middle line:90%
I said, "Jud, take Kathy home.

00:19:20.292 --> 00:19:21.093 align:middle line:90%
Change her clothes.

00:19:21.093 --> 00:19:23.496 align:middle line:90%
She shouldn't be out like this."

00:19:23.496 --> 00:19:27.400 align:middle line:84%
While they were
in the hall there

00:19:27.400 --> 00:19:31.237 align:middle line:84%
and I was trying to send them
home, a brother of my husband's

00:19:31.237 --> 00:19:31.771 align:middle line:90%
came up.

00:19:31.771 --> 00:19:34.306 align:middle line:90%
And he was talking to him.

00:19:34.306 --> 00:19:36.876 align:middle line:90%
And he had gotten word to come.

00:19:36.876 --> 00:19:40.346 align:middle line:84%
And one of his neighbors
was also in the hospital.

00:19:40.346 --> 00:19:44.417 align:middle line:84%
And he came up and started
talking to my brother and all,

00:19:44.417 --> 00:19:47.386 align:middle line:84%
wanting to know what he
was doing at the hospital

00:19:47.386 --> 00:19:49.955 align:middle line:84%
and what he was going
to do that weekend.

00:19:49.955 --> 00:19:52.425 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Well, it looks
like my sister-in-law

00:19:52.425 --> 00:19:53.793 align:middle line:90%
is gonna kick the bucket.

00:19:53.793 --> 00:19:56.162 align:middle line:84%
And I was planning
to go to Athens.

00:19:56.162 --> 00:19:59.598 align:middle line:84%
But I'll stick around
now to be a pallbearer."

00:19:59.598 --> 00:20:02.968 align:middle line:84%
Later I was also
able to talk to him.

00:20:02.968 --> 00:20:04.904 align:middle line:84%
He didn't want to
admit it, but he

00:20:04.904 --> 00:20:08.174 align:middle line:84%
did admit that this
is what he had said.

00:20:08.174 --> 00:20:09.308 align:middle line:90%
And I laughed at him.

00:20:09.308 --> 00:20:11.310 align:middle line:90%
Because it embarrassed him.

00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:15.614 align:middle line:84%
>>It was amazing that I was
never leaving my body, too.

00:20:15.614 --> 00:20:18.884 align:middle line:84%
I was everywhere who
thought about me.

00:20:18.884 --> 00:20:21.053 align:middle line:90%
But I was with my body.

00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:25.357 align:middle line:84%
It means that I was not leaving
the one part for another.

00:20:25.357 --> 00:20:28.494 align:middle line:90%
I was everywhere the same time.

00:20:28.494 --> 00:20:29.662 align:middle line:90%
I could be in New York.

00:20:29.662 --> 00:20:32.431 align:middle line:90%
I could be in Longview, Texas.

00:20:32.431 --> 00:20:34.066 align:middle line:90%
I could be in Moscow.

00:20:34.066 --> 00:20:37.436 align:middle line:84%
I could be in Tbilisi,
Georgia-- in any place.

00:20:37.436 --> 00:20:40.773 align:middle line:84%
There was no distance and
time at that time with me.

00:20:40.773 --> 00:20:42.074 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:20:42.074 --> 00:20:44.343 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: For me, I went to Asia.

00:20:44.343 --> 00:20:46.645 align:middle line:90%
Asia came to me, actually.

00:20:46.645 --> 00:20:48.414 align:middle line:90%
You've heard this over and over.

00:20:48.414 --> 00:20:49.548 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Oh, over and over.

00:20:49.548 --> 00:20:52.017 align:middle line:84%
And people say that
as soon as you're

00:20:52.017 --> 00:20:56.088 align:middle line:84%
into this next state of
existence, that time and space

00:20:56.088 --> 00:20:58.390 align:middle line:84%
as you and I
appreciate it dissolve,

00:20:58.390 --> 00:20:59.825 align:middle line:90%
and there's no such thing.

00:20:59.825 --> 00:21:02.528 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It so begs the
question of are there

00:21:02.528 --> 00:21:03.829 align:middle line:90%
parallel universes?

00:21:03.829 --> 00:21:08.334 align:middle line:84%
Is there no time and
space continuum really?

00:21:08.334 --> 00:21:11.537 align:middle line:84%
Do we live in a
multiple-dimension reality?

00:21:11.537 --> 00:21:14.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, have you ever
asked these questions?

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:16.475 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: I was an
amateur astronomer

00:21:16.475 --> 00:21:18.010 align:middle line:90%
since the age of seven.

00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:18.544 align:middle line:90%
So yes.

00:21:18.544 --> 00:21:19.278 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wow.

00:21:19.278 --> 00:21:23.415 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: And right now,
in physics, there's

00:21:23.415 --> 00:21:26.919 align:middle line:84%
what's called the multiple
worlds interpretation

00:21:26.919 --> 00:21:32.391 align:middle line:84%
of quantum theory, which
is-- some theoreticians say

00:21:32.391 --> 00:21:39.798 align:middle line:84%
that every decision is--
occurs in all dimensions.

00:21:39.798 --> 00:21:45.271 align:middle line:84%
In other words, that when you
make one decision rather than

00:21:45.271 --> 00:21:47.406 align:middle line:84%
another, there's
another part of reality

00:21:47.406 --> 00:21:48.807 align:middle line:90%
that takes off from that point.

00:21:48.807 --> 00:21:50.476 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've heard
that many times, yes.

00:21:50.476 --> 00:21:53.913 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: And so that
there are multiple worlds

00:21:53.913 --> 00:21:56.682 align:middle line:84%
or multiple
dimensions of reality.

00:21:56.682 --> 00:21:59.018 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we make
decisions at various times.

00:21:59.018 --> 00:22:02.855 align:middle line:84%
And that splits off where
our direction goes in life.

00:22:02.855 --> 00:22:04.089 align:middle line:90%
It's fascinating to me.

00:22:04.089 --> 00:22:08.694 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Plato made a similar
point in his works, yeah.

00:22:08.694 --> 00:22:12.398 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now does everybody go
to this light that you explain?

00:22:12.398 --> 00:22:14.733 align:middle line:84%
One of the Facebook
questions is that.

00:22:14.733 --> 00:22:17.536 align:middle line:90%
Is seeing the light real?

00:22:17.536 --> 00:22:18.671 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: I would say this.

00:22:18.671 --> 00:22:21.307 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think
the people who've

00:22:21.307 --> 00:22:26.946 align:middle line:84%
had this experience are
better able to talk to it,

00:22:26.946 --> 00:22:28.113 align:middle line:90%
talk to the point.

00:22:28.113 --> 00:22:35.888 align:middle line:84%
But what they say is that
not only is this light real,

00:22:35.888 --> 00:22:38.490 align:middle line:84%
but that it makes
this existence we

00:22:38.490 --> 00:22:41.493 align:middle line:84%
have now like a
dream by comparison.

00:22:41.493 --> 00:22:43.395 align:middle line:90%
That the reality is not here.

00:22:43.395 --> 00:22:44.597 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The reality is there.

00:22:44.597 --> 00:22:47.366 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: The reality
is in this light.

00:22:47.366 --> 00:22:53.372 align:middle line:84%
And that constantly
people tell me,

00:22:53.372 --> 00:22:55.574 align:middle line:84%
in relating their
near-death experience,

00:22:55.574 --> 00:22:59.845 align:middle line:84%
that when they leave
their body and they almost

00:22:59.845 --> 00:23:03.682 align:middle line:84%
die, that they feel
like they're waking up.

00:23:03.682 --> 00:23:08.520 align:middle line:84%
And that by contrast, this
reality that we're in now

00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:13.792 align:middle line:84%
becomes just like a shadow
or unreal or surrealistic.

00:23:13.792 --> 00:23:20.466 align:middle line:84%
And that the real world
is on the other side.

00:23:20.466 --> 00:23:22.234 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It is an
interesting experience.

00:23:22.234 --> 00:23:26.272 align:middle line:84%
Because the light, for me,
was-- I was in the light.

00:23:26.272 --> 00:23:28.073 align:middle line:84%
It didn't come to me
or I didn't go to it.

00:23:28.073 --> 00:23:30.175 align:middle line:90%
I was in that experience.

00:23:30.175 --> 00:23:33.078 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever, of course,
been approached about the fact

00:23:33.078 --> 00:23:37.316 align:middle line:84%
that this is a lapse
in consciousness,

00:23:37.316 --> 00:23:41.020 align:middle line:84%
that this is a physical
byproduct of losing

00:23:41.020 --> 00:23:42.221 align:middle line:90%
consciousness?

00:23:42.221 --> 00:23:44.156 align:middle line:84%
You've heard this, I'm
sure, a million times.

00:23:44.156 --> 00:23:45.124 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Oh, yes, yes.

00:23:45.124 --> 00:23:47.826 align:middle line:84%
Although I must say I've
never taken that point of view

00:23:47.826 --> 00:23:48.827 align:middle line:90%
seriously.

00:23:48.827 --> 00:23:53.732 align:middle line:84%
I should explain that I do have
an MD, and I'm a psychiatrist.

00:23:53.732 --> 00:23:56.568 align:middle line:84%
But before that, I got
a PhD In philosophy.

00:23:56.568 --> 00:23:58.804 align:middle line:84%
And I was a
philosophy professor.

00:23:58.804 --> 00:24:02.474 align:middle line:84%
And one of the oldest
and most difficult

00:24:02.474 --> 00:24:06.745 align:middle line:84%
questions of philosophy is what
we call the mind-body problem.

00:24:06.745 --> 00:24:10.883 align:middle line:84%
And the real deal is
nobody understands

00:24:10.883 --> 00:24:15.154 align:middle line:84%
what the relationship between
that unique inner experience

00:24:15.154 --> 00:24:18.724 align:middle line:84%
of self awareness or
consciousness on the one hand,

00:24:18.724 --> 00:24:21.694 align:middle line:84%
and on the other hand the
material substance of the body.

00:24:21.694 --> 00:24:24.096 align:middle line:90%
We just don't know.

00:24:24.096 --> 00:24:24.596 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yet.

00:24:24.596 --> 00:24:25.497 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: That's right.

00:24:25.497 --> 00:24:29.435 align:middle line:84%
But the people who
make this claim

00:24:29.435 --> 00:24:32.438 align:middle line:84%
that, oh, these near-death
experiences are just

00:24:32.438 --> 00:24:36.942 align:middle line:84%
hallucinatory effect of the
oxygen cut off to the brain,

00:24:36.942 --> 00:24:38.444 align:middle line:84%
well there are
several difficulties

00:24:38.444 --> 00:24:39.878 align:middle line:90%
with that position.

00:24:39.878 --> 00:24:43.649 align:middle line:84%
Number one is that
I don't know anybody

00:24:43.649 --> 00:24:46.552 align:middle line:84%
who makes that statement
who's really had experience

00:24:46.552 --> 00:24:48.287 align:middle line:90%
interviewing patients.

00:24:48.287 --> 00:24:50.255 align:middle line:84%
What they do is
they read something

00:24:50.255 --> 00:24:51.824 align:middle line:84%
in a magazine or
a book, and then

00:24:51.824 --> 00:24:56.462 align:middle line:84%
they just speculate and put it
together with their ideology.

00:24:56.462 --> 00:24:58.630 align:middle line:84%
People who interview
people, who've

00:24:58.630 --> 00:25:01.333 align:middle line:84%
interviewed lots of
people, as a general rule,

00:25:01.333 --> 00:25:03.602 align:middle line:84%
come to a very different
opinion that this

00:25:03.602 --> 00:25:08.207 align:middle line:84%
is something beyond our
current explanatory models.

00:25:08.207 --> 00:25:16.648 align:middle line:84%
But I think, more importantly,
that the identical experience

00:25:16.648 --> 00:25:18.984 align:middle line:84%
that we call the
near-death experience also

00:25:18.984 --> 00:25:23.989 align:middle line:84%
occurs to the bystanders at the
bedside when somebody does die.

00:25:23.989 --> 00:25:25.824 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The shared death
really does give it

00:25:25.824 --> 00:25:26.625 align:middle line:90%
a different perspective.

00:25:26.625 --> 00:25:27.359 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: That's right.

00:25:27.359 --> 00:25:27.893 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:25:27.893 --> 00:25:29.862 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: And so if the
bystanders, who are not

00:25:29.862 --> 00:25:32.965 align:middle line:84%
ill or injured and the
oxygen flow to their brain

00:25:32.965 --> 00:25:37.736 align:middle line:84%
is not compromised, and yet they
report the identical experience

00:25:37.736 --> 00:25:42.074 align:middle line:84%
to those who are revived
after a close call with death,

00:25:42.074 --> 00:25:45.511 align:middle line:84%
then obviously the cause is
not the oxygen deprivation

00:25:45.511 --> 00:25:46.145 align:middle line:90%
to the brain.

00:25:46.145 --> 00:25:47.846 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, the
shared death experience

00:25:47.846 --> 00:25:50.549 align:middle line:84%
does really kind of
back that up a lot more,

00:25:50.549 --> 00:25:53.185 align:middle line:84%
as we just saw on that
clip, with people around,

00:25:53.185 --> 00:25:57.556 align:middle line:84%
and the evidence of what's
experienced on the outside.

00:25:57.556 --> 00:26:00.492 align:middle line:84%
So when you-- you
had mentioned to me

00:26:00.492 --> 00:26:04.830 align:middle line:84%
that there's a new science
that's really emerging that'll

00:26:04.830 --> 00:26:07.900 align:middle line:84%
help us understand
this a lot more.

00:26:07.900 --> 00:26:09.301 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:26:09.301 --> 00:26:13.238 align:middle line:84%
What I am-- by the
way, I am a logician.

00:26:13.238 --> 00:26:16.675 align:middle line:84%
I don't like to draw
conclusions, in the sense

00:26:16.675 --> 00:26:21.480 align:middle line:90%
that I think-- why hurry?

00:26:21.480 --> 00:26:22.815 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:26:22.815 --> 00:26:27.820 align:middle line:84%
And so I am very conservative
in my pronouncements.

00:26:27.820 --> 00:26:30.289 align:middle line:84%
But nonetheless, in
the last year or so

00:26:30.289 --> 00:26:31.757 align:middle line:84%
I've gotten up to
the point where

00:26:31.757 --> 00:26:34.693 align:middle line:84%
I'm completely
confident to say now

00:26:34.693 --> 00:26:41.800 align:middle line:84%
that we have made a solid
step of genuine progress

00:26:41.800 --> 00:26:45.070 align:middle line:84%
toward rational comprehension
of life after death.

00:26:45.070 --> 00:26:48.807 align:middle line:84%
So that what I am saying is
that in the next few years

00:26:48.807 --> 00:26:53.846 align:middle line:84%
we're going to have entirely
new, purely, absolutely

00:26:53.846 --> 00:26:57.449 align:middle line:84%
rational techniques,
not pseudoscience.

00:26:57.449 --> 00:27:01.253 align:middle line:84%
And I should explain to people,
I am not a parapsychologist.

00:27:01.253 --> 00:27:01.854 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:27:01.854 --> 00:27:03.622 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Parapsychologists
are people

00:27:03.622 --> 00:27:06.225 align:middle line:84%
who are suffering
under the delusion

00:27:06.225 --> 00:27:09.895 align:middle line:84%
that you can use scientific
method as we currently

00:27:09.895 --> 00:27:12.231 align:middle line:90%
have it to prove the afterlife.

00:27:12.231 --> 00:27:15.000 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm saying is
something entirely different--

00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:16.602 align:middle line:90%
that we do now have genuine--

00:27:16.602 --> 00:27:17.135 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wait.

00:27:17.135 --> 00:27:19.505 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to keep on
the edge of your seat.

00:27:19.505 --> 00:27:20.205 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to keep you on
the edge of your seat.

00:27:20.205 --> 00:27:21.440 align:middle line:84%
Just explain this
in just a second.

00:27:21.440 --> 00:27:22.508 align:middle line:90%
We have to take a quick break.

00:27:22.508 --> 00:27:22.774 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Great.

