00:27:56.041 --> 00:27:58.911 align:middle line:84%
about the new sciences
that are emerging.

00:27:58.911 --> 00:27:59.478 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:27:59.478 --> 00:28:01.713 align:middle line:84%
This is very complex,
Lisa, but just

00:28:01.713 --> 00:28:04.550 align:middle line:84%
to give you a
thumbnail sketch of it,

00:28:04.550 --> 00:28:07.853 align:middle line:84%
we have now techniques
where we can actually

00:28:07.853 --> 00:28:12.491 align:middle line:84%
reformat people's minds, for
other reasons than connected

00:28:12.491 --> 00:28:13.659 align:middle line:90%
with near-death experiences.

00:28:13.659 --> 00:28:17.596 align:middle line:84%
This is a way of increasing
critical thinking skills

00:28:17.596 --> 00:28:18.597 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:28:18.597 --> 00:28:20.032 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Through
neurofeedback or--

00:28:20.032 --> 00:28:22.367 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, it's
basically through exercises

00:28:22.367 --> 00:28:26.238 align:middle line:84%
and to sort of eliminate an
incompleteness in Aristotelian

00:28:26.238 --> 00:28:27.139 align:middle line:90%
logic.

00:28:27.139 --> 00:28:30.342 align:middle line:84%
Aristotle's logic is
built into all of us

00:28:30.342 --> 00:28:32.311 align:middle line:90%
because it's been so successful.

00:28:32.311 --> 00:28:34.846 align:middle line:84%
But there was an area
where he sort of left out.

00:28:34.846 --> 00:28:36.582 align:middle line:90%
Now we've filled this in.

00:28:36.582 --> 00:28:40.185 align:middle line:84%
And because of that,
we can help people

00:28:40.185 --> 00:28:44.790 align:middle line:84%
get better analytical thinking
skills and many other benefits

00:28:44.790 --> 00:28:47.759 align:middle line:84%
by this sort of
reformatting of the mind.

00:28:47.759 --> 00:28:51.964 align:middle line:84%
Now, what will happen
is that, once that

00:28:51.964 --> 00:28:54.733 align:middle line:84%
happens, and say you have
several thousand people who

00:28:54.733 --> 00:28:57.970 align:middle line:84%
are working-- equipped
with a new logic,

00:28:57.970 --> 00:29:02.107 align:middle line:84%
in essence, then what's going to
happen with that is that when,

00:29:02.107 --> 00:29:05.210 align:middle line:84%
just by chance, in the
future some of them

00:29:05.210 --> 00:29:07.279 align:middle line:84%
will have near-death
experiences,

00:29:07.279 --> 00:29:08.680 align:middle line:84%
and so they're
going to come back,

00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:10.349 align:middle line:84%
and they're not
going to be limited

00:29:10.349 --> 00:29:13.385 align:middle line:84%
by this problem of
the indescribability

00:29:13.385 --> 00:29:14.052 align:middle line:90%
as the same way.

00:29:14.052 --> 00:29:17.456 align:middle line:84%
So in effect, we can
prepare people's minds

00:29:17.456 --> 00:29:20.425 align:middle line:84%
to articulate this in
such a way as to bring

00:29:20.425 --> 00:29:23.261 align:middle line:84%
us closer to the
experience itself.

00:29:23.261 --> 00:29:26.531 align:middle line:84%
And also we can use
this same information

00:29:26.531 --> 00:29:31.203 align:middle line:84%
to actually be able to track
people and the dying process

00:29:31.203 --> 00:29:33.605 align:middle line:84%
as they go across
to the other side.

00:29:33.605 --> 00:29:36.475 align:middle line:84%
And right now this all
sounds pretty incredible.

00:29:36.475 --> 00:29:40.879 align:middle line:84%
But stay tuned, because
this is on the way.

00:29:40.879 --> 00:29:42.481 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is the
emerging sciences.

00:29:42.481 --> 00:29:42.814 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: That's right.

00:29:42.814 --> 00:29:45.183 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is getting rid
of the old scientific ways

00:29:45.183 --> 00:29:47.753 align:middle line:84%
of explaining things into
new realms of thinking.

00:29:47.753 --> 00:29:49.421 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Entirely new
realm of thinking.

00:29:49.421 --> 00:29:50.489 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's perfect.

00:29:50.489 --> 00:29:50.956 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:29:50.956 --> 00:29:55.627 align:middle line:84%
So as we were explaining earlier
about this light that happens,

00:29:55.627 --> 00:29:57.062 align:middle line:84%
that people go
through this tunnel

00:29:57.062 --> 00:29:58.463 align:middle line:84%
and so forth,
there's another clip

00:29:58.463 --> 00:30:00.532 align:middle line:84%
that I want to show
you about the light

00:30:00.532 --> 00:30:02.968 align:middle line:84%
that people experience in
going through this near-death

00:30:02.968 --> 00:30:03.735 align:middle line:90%
experience.

00:30:03.735 --> 00:30:06.571 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:30:06.571 --> 00:30:08.540 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:30:08.540 --> 00:30:11.209 align:middle line:84%
>>They describe to
us how they seem

00:30:11.209 --> 00:30:14.079 align:middle line:84%
to be drawn into an
enclosure of some sort.

00:30:14.079 --> 00:30:16.648 align:middle line:90%
They often call it a tunnel.

00:30:16.648 --> 00:30:18.784 align:middle line:84%
And they go through this
tunnel quite rapidly.

00:30:18.784 --> 00:30:20.585 align:middle line:84%
And they come out
of the other side

00:30:20.585 --> 00:30:25.424 align:middle line:84%
into an incredibly brilliant
and warm and loving light.

00:30:25.424 --> 00:30:29.594 align:middle line:84%
>>Don't know exactly how I
entered the tunnel or just

00:30:29.594 --> 00:30:30.462 align:middle line:90%
at what point.

00:30:30.462 --> 00:30:33.165 align:middle line:84%
But it was when the
guards had asked me.

00:30:33.165 --> 00:30:34.166 align:middle line:90%
And I said yes.

00:30:34.166 --> 00:30:39.337 align:middle line:84%
And I feel myself going
in an upward motion.

00:30:39.337 --> 00:30:45.077 align:middle line:84%
The tunnel is not too big,
just room for one person

00:30:45.077 --> 00:30:47.112 align:middle line:90%
to go one at a time.

00:30:47.112 --> 00:30:51.516 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't touch you, or didn't
reach out and touch the walls.

00:30:51.516 --> 00:30:52.484 align:middle line:90%
But it's black.

00:30:52.484 --> 00:30:55.620 align:middle line:84%
And I feel myself
going up and looking

00:30:55.620 --> 00:30:58.724 align:middle line:84%
at light, bright light
at the end of the tunnel.

00:30:58.724 --> 00:31:02.561 align:middle line:84%
And the next, as I'm going
along, I see the gray area.

00:31:02.561 --> 00:31:07.799 align:middle line:84%
But I did not stop to go in
and see just what was going on.

00:31:07.799 --> 00:31:13.972 align:middle line:84%
I went on to come out into this
beautiful pasture, valley land.

00:31:13.972 --> 00:31:15.874 align:middle line:90%
Flowers.

00:31:15.874 --> 00:31:18.510 align:middle line:90%
Bright, beautiful light.

00:31:18.510 --> 00:31:22.481 align:middle line:84%
Brilliant color-- nothing
here is like it at all.

00:31:22.481 --> 00:31:23.448 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:31:23.448 --> 00:31:24.916 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: She's
talking about that as

00:31:24.916 --> 00:31:27.419 align:middle line:84%
if it's a present-time
experience, right?

00:31:27.419 --> 00:31:28.019 align:middle line:90%
Is that common?

00:31:28.019 --> 00:31:29.354 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:31:29.354 --> 00:31:35.627 align:middle line:84%
When people are relating a very
vivid and memorable experience,

00:31:35.627 --> 00:31:38.864 align:middle line:84%
even if it occurred
to them in the past,

00:31:38.864 --> 00:31:40.632 align:middle line:84%
they resort to a
figure of speech

00:31:40.632 --> 00:31:45.203 align:middle line:84%
which is called analogy,
which is talking about,

00:31:45.203 --> 00:31:47.739 align:middle line:84%
for example, talking
about a past experience

00:31:47.739 --> 00:31:48.707 align:middle line:90%
in the present tense.

00:31:48.707 --> 00:31:49.741 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so
that's how we know

00:31:49.741 --> 00:31:50.942 align:middle line:90%
that she's telling the truth.

00:31:50.942 --> 00:31:54.980 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, it shows that
she is, even now, after years,

00:31:54.980 --> 00:31:59.284 align:middle line:84%
she's experiencing the
vividness of this experience.

00:31:59.284 --> 00:32:01.019 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how can
this information

00:32:01.019 --> 00:32:04.723 align:middle line:84%
help us, where we go
through tragic disasters

00:32:04.723 --> 00:32:06.658 align:middle line:84%
like a tsunami,
or we lose people

00:32:06.658 --> 00:32:08.994 align:middle line:90%
in a tragic events like a 9/11.

00:32:08.994 --> 00:32:10.862 align:middle line:90%
How does this help us?

00:32:10.862 --> 00:32:13.732 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, Lisa, one thing
I have observed over the years

00:32:13.732 --> 00:32:17.869 align:middle line:84%
that I think is pretty much
clear about these experiences

00:32:17.869 --> 00:32:20.238 align:middle line:84%
is that they do
give people comfort

00:32:20.238 --> 00:32:21.973 align:middle line:90%
who've lost loved ones to death.

00:32:21.973 --> 00:32:23.341 align:middle line:90%
That is the fact.

00:32:23.341 --> 00:32:24.276 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How?

00:32:24.276 --> 00:32:27.746 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, first
of all, for many people

00:32:27.746 --> 00:32:30.916 align:middle line:84%
this whole idea of an afterlife
is something vague and abstract

00:32:30.916 --> 00:32:33.418 align:middle line:84%
that maybe they encounter
in their religious belief,

00:32:33.418 --> 00:32:35.720 align:middle line:90%
but it's not filled out.

00:32:35.720 --> 00:32:39.858 align:middle line:84%
But this, from people
who actually got there

00:32:39.858 --> 00:32:44.196 align:middle line:84%
to the cusp of the other world
and are able to talk about even

00:32:44.196 --> 00:32:47.132 align:middle line:84%
then they felt great, and
there was this love and so on.

00:32:47.132 --> 00:32:49.668 align:middle line:84%
And that is a very
comforting message

00:32:49.668 --> 00:32:52.003 align:middle line:84%
to people who've
lost loved ones.

00:32:52.003 --> 00:32:57.042 align:middle line:84%
That said, I must go on
to say that, you know,

00:32:57.042 --> 00:33:00.779 align:middle line:84%
even people who've had profound
near-death experiences, they

00:33:00.779 --> 00:33:03.014 align:middle line:84%
say that when they lose
a loved one to death,

00:33:03.014 --> 00:33:04.382 align:middle line:90%
they still miss them.

00:33:04.382 --> 00:33:05.383 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, of course.

00:33:05.383 --> 00:33:05.684 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:33:05.684 --> 00:33:06.318 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yeah.

00:33:06.318 --> 00:33:09.387 align:middle line:84%
But it does give, I
think, people a comfort

00:33:09.387 --> 00:33:13.024 align:middle line:84%
to realize that in the future
they're going to be reunited

00:33:13.024 --> 00:33:15.093 align:middle line:84%
with their loved ones
they lost to death.

00:33:15.093 --> 00:33:17.729 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you hear that,
that they're in a better place.

00:33:17.729 --> 00:33:19.397 align:middle line:84%
You've heard that
phrase many times.

00:33:19.397 --> 00:33:21.700 align:middle line:84%
Well, this is maybe
the example of that.

00:33:21.700 --> 00:33:22.267 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yeah.

00:33:22.267 --> 00:33:22.534 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All right.

00:33:22.534 --> 00:33:25.170 align:middle line:84%
Here's another clip from
the movie "Life After Life"

00:33:25.170 --> 00:33:28.173 align:middle line:84%
about being in
that better place.

00:33:28.173 --> 00:33:29.074 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:33:29.074 --> 00:33:32.744 align:middle line:84%
>>If you imagine this
panorama of your life

00:33:32.744 --> 00:33:36.748 align:middle line:84%
as like a still pond, and
each action in your life

00:33:36.748 --> 00:33:39.818 align:middle line:84%
is like a pebble which
you flip into that pond.

00:33:39.818 --> 00:33:42.320 align:middle line:84%
At the point where that
pebble impacts on the surface,

00:33:42.320 --> 00:33:43.655 align:middle line:90%
you see ripples going out.

00:33:43.655 --> 00:33:44.422 align:middle line:90%
>>Right.

00:33:44.422 --> 00:33:49.127 align:middle line:84%
>>But he said that as these
ripples and this panorama

00:33:49.127 --> 00:33:54.132 align:middle line:84%
impinge on others, then you can
see the secondary effects going

00:33:54.132 --> 00:33:56.768 align:middle line:84%
off from those people
in the form of ripples.

00:33:56.768 --> 00:33:57.269 align:middle line:90%
>>I see.

00:33:57.269 --> 00:34:00.472 align:middle line:84%
>>So I think it
illustrates how tied in we

00:34:00.472 --> 00:34:03.875 align:middle line:84%
all are to one another in
this life, how profoundly

00:34:03.875 --> 00:34:08.013 align:middle line:84%
our actions and our
feelings affect others.

00:34:08.013 --> 00:34:11.315 align:middle line:84%
And of course, in this life
review we're made aware of that

00:34:11.315 --> 00:34:12.984 align:middle line:90%
in a very profound way.

00:34:12.984 --> 00:34:13.752 align:middle line:90%
>>Yeah.

00:34:13.752 --> 00:34:18.422 align:middle line:84%
>>And people say, too, that
it's not the events in your life

00:34:18.422 --> 00:34:21.626 align:middle line:84%
that you would necessarily
expect which get reviewed.

00:34:21.626 --> 00:34:23.862 align:middle line:84%
It's not the big
accomplishments, but rather

00:34:23.862 --> 00:34:26.697 align:middle line:84%
the simple acts of
kindness, often things

00:34:26.697 --> 00:34:28.300 align:middle line:84%
that you would even
have forgotten.

00:34:28.300 --> 00:34:29.634 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:34:29.634 --> 00:34:31.603 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Have you ever
heard the same type

00:34:31.603 --> 00:34:35.139 align:middle line:84%
of experience of
someone who has--

00:34:35.139 --> 00:34:38.009 align:middle line:84%
like that commit suicide
and comes back from that.

00:34:38.009 --> 00:34:39.377 align:middle line:90%
>>Thank you for that question.

00:34:42.179 --> 00:34:46.952 align:middle line:84%
We-- studies have shown that
the near-death experiences

00:34:46.952 --> 00:34:50.989 align:middle line:84%
of suicide attempters are no
different from those of people

00:34:50.989 --> 00:34:54.025 align:middle line:84%
who come close to death
from other causes.

00:34:54.025 --> 00:34:57.329 align:middle line:84%
But in the studies
that were done of this,

00:34:57.329 --> 00:34:58.997 align:middle line:84%
they interviewed
all the patients

00:34:58.997 --> 00:35:01.333 align:middle line:84%
who came into the hospital
over a period of time

00:35:01.333 --> 00:35:02.968 align:middle line:84%
who had attempted
to kill themselves,

00:35:02.968 --> 00:35:08.139 align:middle line:84%
almost died as a
result, but survived it.

00:35:08.139 --> 00:35:09.507 align:middle line:90%
And they interviewed them.

00:35:09.507 --> 00:35:11.977 align:middle line:84%
And they found that some
did and some did not

00:35:11.977 --> 00:35:13.345 align:middle line:90%
have a near-death experience.

00:35:13.345 --> 00:35:13.878 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:35:13.878 --> 00:35:16.548 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Then following
these two groups of patients

00:35:16.548 --> 00:35:19.651 align:middle line:84%
afterward, they found a
remarkable occurrence.

00:35:19.651 --> 00:35:23.088 align:middle line:84%
And that is that while
the patients who did not

00:35:23.088 --> 00:35:26.157 align:middle line:84%
have a near-death
experience continued

00:35:26.157 --> 00:35:28.526 align:middle line:84%
to have a high rate
of subsequent attempts

00:35:28.526 --> 00:35:31.129 align:middle line:84%
to kill themselves,
the patients who did

00:35:31.129 --> 00:35:35.333 align:middle line:84%
have a near-death experience
had an essentially zero rate

00:35:35.333 --> 00:35:37.769 align:middle line:84%
of any further attempts
to kill themselves.

00:35:37.769 --> 00:35:40.305 align:middle line:84%
And when interviewed
about this, what they said

00:35:40.305 --> 00:35:44.075 align:middle line:84%
was not that they felt that,
had this gone to completion,

00:35:44.075 --> 00:35:46.878 align:middle line:84%
they would have ended
up in a terrible hell,

00:35:46.878 --> 00:35:50.048 align:middle line:84%
but rather, that they
learned from their experience

00:35:50.048 --> 00:35:54.352 align:middle line:84%
that even when times are
tough, life has a purpose.

00:35:54.352 --> 00:35:58.390 align:middle line:84%
And also they realized that,
had this gone to completion,

00:35:58.390 --> 00:36:00.759 align:middle line:84%
they would have had to
have seen, empathically,

00:36:00.759 --> 00:36:04.829 align:middle line:84%
the after effects of this, that
they would have experienced

00:36:04.829 --> 00:36:07.165 align:middle line:84%
the pain and hurt
that they had brought

00:36:07.165 --> 00:36:10.435 align:middle line:84%
about in the lives of
those who they left behind.

00:36:10.435 --> 00:36:12.904 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Through the ripple
effect in that panoramic life

00:36:12.904 --> 00:36:13.805 align:middle line:90%
review.

00:36:13.805 --> 00:36:17.575 align:middle line:84%
So now, in the same sense, if
someone was, say, in a coma,

00:36:17.575 --> 00:36:19.944 align:middle line:84%
could the people
around them that

00:36:19.944 --> 00:36:24.049 align:middle line:84%
love them, like children
or other loved ones,

00:36:24.049 --> 00:36:28.653 align:middle line:84%
hold them back and keep them
into this life with intention,

00:36:28.653 --> 00:36:29.154 align:middle line:90%
with will?

00:36:29.154 --> 00:36:30.055 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever seen that?

00:36:30.055 --> 00:36:31.056 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, you
know, actually, I've

00:36:31.056 --> 00:36:32.690 align:middle line:84%
heard a few people
over the years

00:36:32.690 --> 00:36:38.396 align:middle line:84%
tell me that, yes, that they
did feel that they were brought

00:36:38.396 --> 00:36:41.332 align:middle line:84%
back by the prayers
of their loved ones.

00:36:41.332 --> 00:36:43.935 align:middle line:84%
Or sometimes when
they're given a choice,

00:36:43.935 --> 00:36:45.570 align:middle line:84%
they can either go
on in this light

00:36:45.570 --> 00:36:48.907 align:middle line:84%
or they can go back to the
life they've been leading.

00:36:48.907 --> 00:36:52.077 align:middle line:84%
They choose to come back not
because that's what they want.

00:36:52.077 --> 00:36:54.245 align:middle line:84%
They say, for themselves,
they would rather

00:36:54.245 --> 00:36:55.947 align:middle line:84%
have stayed in the
light, but they

00:36:55.947 --> 00:36:58.917 align:middle line:84%
choose to come back on the
behalf of other people.

00:36:58.917 --> 00:37:03.154 align:middle line:84%
Like they say they chose to come
back because, most commonly,

00:37:03.154 --> 00:37:05.123 align:middle line:84%
because they have small
children left to raise.

00:37:05.123 --> 00:37:08.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes, yes, yes.

00:37:08.660 --> 00:37:11.429 align:middle line:84%
Someone from Facebook
is saying, Dee,

00:37:11.429 --> 00:37:15.533 align:middle line:84%
his uncle has passed several
times-- no, has already passed.

00:37:15.533 --> 00:37:19.604 align:middle line:84%
And she had three consecutive
dreams of him and his death.

00:37:19.604 --> 00:37:22.006 align:middle line:90%
Did Dee cause this?

00:37:22.006 --> 00:37:24.943 align:middle line:90%
And why does this happen?

00:37:24.943 --> 00:37:27.445 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, Dee, I don't
know exactly why it happens,

00:37:27.445 --> 00:37:29.881 align:middle line:84%
but I do know this-- that
the experience you're

00:37:29.881 --> 00:37:32.150 align:middle line:84%
relating there is
just very common.

00:37:32.150 --> 00:37:34.752 align:middle line:84%
That it's a very
common phenomenon

00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:37.989 align:middle line:84%
that within a certain period of
time after the death of a loved

00:37:37.989 --> 00:37:40.592 align:middle line:84%
one, that people
will have what are

00:37:40.592 --> 00:37:42.827 align:middle line:90%
called apparitional experiences.

00:37:42.827 --> 00:37:46.297 align:middle line:84%
And these occur in
three circumstances.

00:37:46.297 --> 00:37:51.035 align:middle line:84%
One, as in the description
you're giving there, a dream.

00:37:51.035 --> 00:37:53.605 align:middle line:84%
Now, often-- I don't
know about your case,

00:37:53.605 --> 00:37:56.040 align:middle line:84%
but very often people
tell me that they

00:37:56.040 --> 00:38:00.145 align:middle line:84%
have to call it a dream
because they were asleep.

00:38:00.145 --> 00:38:01.980 align:middle line:90%
But it didn't seem like a dream.

00:38:01.980 --> 00:38:04.616 align:middle line:90%
It had the quality of reality.

00:38:04.616 --> 00:38:07.519 align:middle line:84%
Another kind of common
locale for apparitions

00:38:07.519 --> 00:38:10.588 align:middle line:84%
is people will say that as
they're in the bed at night

00:38:10.588 --> 00:38:12.123 align:middle line:84%
and they're still
awake, but they

00:38:12.123 --> 00:38:15.226 align:middle line:84%
see the apparition of
the deceased person

00:38:15.226 --> 00:38:17.162 align:middle line:90%
there at their bedside.

00:38:17.162 --> 00:38:19.330 align:middle line:84%
And then the third
group are people

00:38:19.330 --> 00:38:21.999 align:middle line:84%
who say that in the middle
of the day, when they're

00:38:21.999 --> 00:38:24.903 align:middle line:84%
fully conscious and
in waking awareness,

00:38:24.903 --> 00:38:27.438 align:middle line:84%
that they have apparitions
of the deceased.

00:38:27.438 --> 00:38:30.008 align:middle line:84%
So the experience
you're describing

00:38:30.008 --> 00:38:32.610 align:middle line:84%
is something that
literally goes back--

00:38:32.610 --> 00:38:37.282 align:middle line:84%
there are descriptions of this
even going back to antiquity.

00:38:37.282 --> 00:38:37.916 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:38:37.916 --> 00:38:38.716 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Oh, yes.

00:38:38.716 --> 00:38:42.253 align:middle line:84%
This is part and parcel
of being a human being.

00:38:42.253 --> 00:38:44.989 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The same thing
happened to me, Dee.

00:38:44.989 --> 00:38:47.559 align:middle line:84%
Before my husband's
grandfather passed.

00:38:47.559 --> 00:38:49.427 align:middle line:84%
We were driving away
from the hospital,

00:38:49.427 --> 00:38:50.595 align:middle line:90%
and he was still alive.

00:38:50.595 --> 00:38:52.764 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I'll be right back.

00:38:52.764 --> 00:38:55.166 align:middle line:90%
And I fell into this deep--

00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:55.767 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Trance

00:38:55.767 --> 00:38:56.834 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --trance.

00:38:56.834 --> 00:39:00.772 align:middle line:84%
And he came really clearly to me
and said, I'm going to go now.

00:39:00.772 --> 00:39:01.806 align:middle line:90%
And I woke up.

00:39:01.806 --> 00:39:05.343 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I have a message
for you, to my husband.

00:39:05.343 --> 00:39:08.146 align:middle line:84%
And he's driving, thinking,
what just happened?

00:39:08.146 --> 00:39:10.448 align:middle line:84%
And then he passed
several days out.

00:39:10.448 --> 00:39:11.316 align:middle line:90%
So you've heard this.

00:39:11.316 --> 00:39:12.250 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Oh, yes.

00:39:12.250 --> 00:39:12.917 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, you're kidding.

00:39:12.917 --> 00:39:15.220 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: You know, these
shared death experiences don't

00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:17.422 align:middle line:84%
happen-- they don't
have to happen

00:39:17.422 --> 00:39:19.224 align:middle line:90%
right there at the bedside.

00:39:19.224 --> 00:39:19.791 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:39:19.791 --> 00:39:21.226 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: I've had
many cases where

00:39:21.226 --> 00:39:23.828 align:middle line:84%
people would say that
even across the city

00:39:23.828 --> 00:39:27.065 align:middle line:84%
or across the state or in
another part of the country,

00:39:27.065 --> 00:39:30.235 align:middle line:84%
that the moment their loved
one died in some other place,

00:39:30.235 --> 00:39:31.869 align:middle line:90%
they will realize that.

00:39:31.869 --> 00:39:34.339 align:middle line:84%
And then a while later
they get the phone

00:39:34.339 --> 00:39:36.541 align:middle line:90%
call that it had happened.

00:39:36.541 --> 00:39:38.576 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Carina is asking--
Carina from Facebook--

00:39:38.576 --> 00:39:41.112 align:middle line:84%
and thanks for your comments
coming in, by the way.

00:39:41.112 --> 00:39:43.314 align:middle line:84%
She had a similar--
she wants to find out

00:39:43.314 --> 00:39:45.883 align:middle line:84%
if there's something similar
between a near-death experience

00:39:45.883 --> 00:39:47.385 align:middle line:90%
and passing out from pain.

00:39:47.385 --> 00:39:49.787 align:middle line:84%
She had an unusual experience
where she passed out

00:39:49.787 --> 00:39:50.855 align:middle line:90%
from a ruptured appendix.

00:39:50.855 --> 00:39:51.723 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes, Carina.

00:39:51.723 --> 00:39:54.993 align:middle line:84%
What I think is going on here
is there's a kind of continuum.

00:39:54.993 --> 00:39:57.328 align:middle line:84%
And I mean a
ruptured appendix-- I

00:39:57.328 --> 00:39:59.864 align:middle line:84%
don't know what your doctors
might have told you about that,

00:39:59.864 --> 00:40:02.533 align:middle line:84%
but that's a
dangerous situation.

00:40:02.533 --> 00:40:06.604 align:middle line:84%
And you were in very grave
states at that point.

00:40:06.604 --> 00:40:09.641 align:middle line:84%
So you know, this
is a continuum.

00:40:09.641 --> 00:40:17.048 align:middle line:84%
And people who, as the
call is-- the closer you

00:40:17.048 --> 00:40:21.719 align:middle line:84%
get to this death, the
more elements of these

00:40:21.719 --> 00:40:22.353 align:middle line:90%
that you have.

00:40:22.353 --> 00:40:22.920 align:middle line:90%
So yeah.

00:40:22.920 --> 00:40:25.390 align:middle line:90%
There's kind of continuum.

00:40:25.390 --> 00:40:30.328 align:middle line:84%
So that people who are in severe
states, as you're describing,

00:40:30.328 --> 00:40:32.597 align:middle line:84%
can have parts of this
near-death experience.

00:40:32.597 --> 00:40:33.431 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:40:33.431 --> 00:40:34.132 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:40:34.132 --> 00:40:36.234 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's an
overarching theme here.

00:40:36.234 --> 00:40:39.203 align:middle line:84%
And basically it's--
what is this teaching us?

00:40:39.203 --> 00:40:43.641 align:middle line:84%
What is the purpose of these
experiences and sharing them

00:40:43.641 --> 00:40:44.409 align:middle line:90%
with other people?

00:40:44.409 --> 00:40:46.711 align:middle line:90%
What is this?

00:40:46.711 --> 00:40:49.147 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Everybody that
I know who comes back

00:40:49.147 --> 00:40:51.416 align:middle line:84%
from one of these
very transcendent

00:40:51.416 --> 00:40:55.653 align:middle line:84%
near-death experiences, whatever
they happened to be chasing

00:40:55.653 --> 00:40:58.823 align:middle line:84%
in life, I mean, as a
psychiatrist and a person,

00:40:58.823 --> 00:41:01.392 align:middle line:84%
I know that most people
are chasing something.

00:41:01.392 --> 00:41:02.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The dream.

00:41:02.160 --> 00:41:02.727 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yeah.

00:41:02.727 --> 00:41:04.362 align:middle line:90%
Like me, it's knowledge.

00:41:04.362 --> 00:41:07.765 align:middle line:84%
Some people chase
power or fame or money

00:41:07.765 --> 00:41:09.167 align:middle line:90%
or any of these other things.

00:41:09.167 --> 00:41:11.536 align:middle line:84%
But when people come
back from this, whatever

00:41:11.536 --> 00:41:14.105 align:middle line:84%
they were chasing,
they say what this

00:41:14.105 --> 00:41:17.008 align:middle line:84%
is all about is
learning to love.

00:41:17.008 --> 00:41:21.045 align:middle line:84%
Because they say that's
what came up in this review

00:41:21.045 --> 00:41:25.450 align:middle line:84%
is that the most important thing
we can do while we're alive

00:41:25.450 --> 00:41:28.886 align:middle line:84%
is to learn how to love,
which is not an easy task.

00:41:28.886 --> 00:41:31.489 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, it shows it very
clearly in the movie "Life

00:41:31.489 --> 00:41:35.093 align:middle line:84%
After Life," of explanations
of what people got back

00:41:35.093 --> 00:41:36.494 align:middle line:84%
from their near-death
experiences.

00:41:36.494 --> 00:41:38.363 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:41:38.363 --> 00:41:39.197 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:41:39.197 --> 00:41:41.532 align:middle line:84%
>>It's so touching to
me that in the closing

00:41:41.532 --> 00:41:46.904 align:middle line:84%
moments of their life, that
so many people come back

00:41:46.904 --> 00:41:51.676 align:middle line:84%
reporting that what was most
important to them at this time

00:41:51.676 --> 00:41:55.046 align:middle line:84%
was love, the
question of how they

00:41:55.046 --> 00:41:57.281 align:middle line:84%
had loved their
fellow human beings.

00:41:57.281 --> 00:42:00.084 align:middle line:84%
>>It had a lot of effects
in changing my life.

00:42:00.084 --> 00:42:04.288 align:middle line:84%
It's made me a more
understanding person of others.

00:42:04.288 --> 00:42:07.058 align:middle line:84%
I know I don't have the
right to take my life.

00:42:07.058 --> 00:42:08.993 align:middle line:90%
I didn't want to return.

00:42:08.993 --> 00:42:10.895 align:middle line:90%
And I would love to go back.

00:42:10.895 --> 00:42:12.930 align:middle line:90%
Someday I will.

00:42:12.930 --> 00:42:16.067 align:middle line:84%
And then I hopefully can stay
and not have to come back

00:42:16.067 --> 00:42:18.302 align:middle line:90%
and try again.

00:42:18.302 --> 00:42:21.038 align:middle line:84%
But I know I cannot take
my life and go there.

00:42:21.038 --> 00:42:23.841 align:middle line:90%
Things would not work out right.

00:42:23.841 --> 00:42:26.878 align:middle line:84%
But I think I'm a better
person about watching

00:42:26.878 --> 00:42:29.814 align:middle line:84%
for the needs of others and
not being always selfish.

00:42:29.814 --> 00:42:31.182 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I'm still selfish.

00:42:31.182 --> 00:42:32.984 align:middle line:90%
I'm still a human.

00:42:32.984 --> 00:42:35.920 align:middle line:84%
But it has changed
my way of thinking.

00:42:35.920 --> 00:42:38.456 align:middle line:84%
>>How to love other
people and how

00:42:38.456 --> 00:42:43.027 align:middle line:84%
to-- how to forgive
and to put yourself

00:42:43.027 --> 00:42:49.267 align:middle line:84%
in the place of other people
in order to understand them.

00:42:49.267 --> 00:42:50.868 align:middle line:84%
And that's something
that you have

00:42:50.868 --> 00:42:56.641 align:middle line:84%
to do in order to love people
and in order to love yourself.

00:42:56.641 --> 00:43:03.581 align:middle line:84%
Because if you hold grudges
and you-- it hurts you.

00:43:03.581 --> 00:43:05.683 align:middle line:90%
And it hurts the other people.

00:43:05.683 --> 00:43:11.022 align:middle line:84%
And it's a barrier to
love if you can't forgive.

00:43:11.022 --> 00:43:14.892 align:middle line:84%
You don't necessarily have to
forget when people hurt you,

00:43:14.892 --> 00:43:19.363 align:middle line:84%
but you have to understand
them and forgive them.

00:43:19.363 --> 00:43:23.768 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that is the
most important thing about love

00:43:23.768 --> 00:43:25.169 align:middle line:90%
that I've learned.

00:43:25.169 --> 00:43:28.473 align:middle line:84%
And how to look
at how we're alike

00:43:28.473 --> 00:43:30.208 align:middle line:90%
rather than how we're different.

00:43:30.208 --> 00:43:32.810 align:middle line:84%
>>This is the main message
which I brought back,

00:43:32.810 --> 00:43:36.047 align:middle line:84%
that love is what
cannot be changed.

00:43:36.047 --> 00:43:38.249 align:middle line:90%
This is everlasting.

00:43:38.249 --> 00:43:41.953 align:middle line:84%
And love is with
life always together.

00:43:41.953 --> 00:43:46.257 align:middle line:84%
Love-- what keeps
this world alive.

00:43:46.257 --> 00:43:49.126 align:middle line:90%
Love as an eternity.

00:43:49.126 --> 00:43:54.265 align:middle line:90%
Love as a basic of humankind.

00:43:54.265 --> 00:43:58.369 align:middle line:84%
And we are alive
because of love.

00:43:58.369 --> 00:43:59.203 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:43:59.203 --> 00:43:59.904 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:43:59.904 --> 00:44:02.373 align:middle line:84%
And if we could all
bring that experience

00:44:02.373 --> 00:44:04.709 align:middle line:84%
into our current
waking reality--

00:44:04.709 --> 00:44:07.378 align:middle line:84%
that's what happened
to me when I came back

00:44:07.378 --> 00:44:09.013 align:middle line:90%
from that experience.

00:44:09.013 --> 00:44:13.017 align:middle line:84%
And when I did come back
in, and after several months

00:44:13.017 --> 00:44:17.154 align:middle line:84%
of severe memory
loss, I realized

00:44:17.154 --> 00:44:19.657 align:middle line:84%
that the man that
was there to help me

00:44:19.657 --> 00:44:25.062 align:middle line:84%
was the man I had broken up with
before I had this experience

00:44:25.062 --> 00:44:26.831 align:middle line:84%
and then now is the
man I'm married to.

00:44:26.831 --> 00:44:29.267 align:middle line:90%
So it is about love.

00:44:29.267 --> 00:44:32.236 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately,
all is about love.

00:44:32.236 --> 00:44:38.809 align:middle line:84%
But how does that help someone
who has lost someone they love?

00:44:38.809 --> 00:44:44.649 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, again, what
I think is that it's-- that

00:44:44.649 --> 00:44:48.286 align:middle line:84%
you're always going to
miss the person who died.

00:44:48.286 --> 00:44:51.455 align:middle line:84%
But to me it's very
comforting to know that,

00:44:51.455 --> 00:44:56.294 align:middle line:84%
as based on literally
thousands upon thousands

00:44:56.294 --> 00:45:01.399 align:middle line:84%
upon thousands of cases, that
what people say is that you do

00:45:01.399 --> 00:45:03.167 align:middle line:90%
see them again.

00:45:03.167 --> 00:45:05.069 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, that
is very comforting.

00:45:05.069 --> 00:45:08.005 align:middle line:84%
Even-- actually, Diane's
asking, what about pets?

00:45:08.005 --> 00:45:08.806 align:middle line:90%
Do you see them?

00:45:08.806 --> 00:45:10.007 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever heard anything?

00:45:10.007 --> 00:45:13.711 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well, you know,
Diane, not many cases

00:45:13.711 --> 00:45:17.982 align:middle line:84%
of near-death experiences
have I interviewed

00:45:17.982 --> 00:45:22.119 align:middle line:84%
where the people did
see a deceased pet.

00:45:22.119 --> 00:45:24.589 align:middle line:90%
However, there have been some.

00:45:24.589 --> 00:45:30.528 align:middle line:84%
And-- now, this part is just
a conjecture and an intuition.

00:45:30.528 --> 00:45:36.133 align:middle line:84%
But I have a sense that
probably that part of it

00:45:36.133 --> 00:45:37.635 align:middle line:90%
is under reported.

00:45:37.635 --> 00:45:42.206 align:middle line:84%
And the reason is that, in
my grief counseling practice,

00:45:42.206 --> 00:45:45.943 align:middle line:84%
I see people who are
there because they're

00:45:45.943 --> 00:45:48.379 align:middle line:90%
grieving the loss of a pet.

00:45:48.379 --> 00:45:53.351 align:middle line:84%
And so I know how powerful
an experience that is.

00:45:53.351 --> 00:45:56.554 align:middle line:84%
And also, people
in that situation

00:45:56.554 --> 00:45:59.357 align:middle line:84%
generally tell me that they
feel embarrassed because they're

00:45:59.357 --> 00:46:02.226 align:middle line:84%
afraid to talk about
their family with this.

00:46:02.226 --> 00:46:03.995 align:middle line:84%
They don't think
their family will

00:46:03.995 --> 00:46:07.398 align:middle line:84%
be understanding, that it's
a sign of weakness, blah,

00:46:07.398 --> 00:46:08.599 align:middle line:90%
blah, blah, all those things.

00:46:08.599 --> 00:46:10.901 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No, I've heard
that the loss of a pet is--

00:46:10.901 --> 00:46:12.169 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes, it absolutely is.

00:46:12.169 --> 00:46:14.338 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: --almost as bad
as the loss of a loved one.

00:46:14.338 --> 00:46:16.540 align:middle line:84%
Or it will reignite the
pain of a lost loved one.

00:46:16.540 --> 00:46:17.241 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: It does.

00:46:17.241 --> 00:46:20.478 align:middle line:84%
And so what I would say in
answer to Diane's question

00:46:20.478 --> 00:46:23.914 align:middle line:84%
is that I don't know
many cases of that,

00:46:23.914 --> 00:46:25.850 align:middle line:84%
but I think there are
probably many more.

00:46:25.850 --> 00:46:28.753 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
probably that that

00:46:28.753 --> 00:46:31.555 align:middle line:84%
is something that would be
too personal for many people

00:46:31.555 --> 00:46:32.790 align:middle line:90%
to relate.

00:46:32.790 --> 00:46:33.958 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, I'm sure.

00:46:33.958 --> 00:46:37.261 align:middle line:84%
And it's definitely because
the animals themselves

00:46:37.261 --> 00:46:38.696 align:middle line:90%
are so unconditionally loving.

00:46:38.696 --> 00:46:41.165 align:middle line:84%
It does fit right
into that concept

00:46:41.165 --> 00:46:44.835 align:middle line:84%
of the overarching theme
here, which is love.

00:46:44.835 --> 00:46:48.639 align:middle line:84%
Love is experienced on the other
side that you've heard about.

00:46:48.639 --> 00:46:51.709 align:middle line:84%
It teaches us back
into this reality

00:46:51.709 --> 00:46:54.145 align:middle line:84%
that love is the
most important thing.

00:46:54.145 --> 00:46:57.448 align:middle line:84%
As you said to me when I
very first spoke to you,

00:46:57.448 --> 00:46:59.150 align:middle line:84%
love is the most
important thing.

00:46:59.150 --> 00:47:00.251 align:middle line:90%
And it's beautifully said.

00:47:00.251 --> 00:47:01.419 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Well, it really is.

00:47:01.419 --> 00:47:02.053 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It is.

00:47:02.053 --> 00:47:03.587 align:middle line:84%
Another one of our
Facebook questions

00:47:03.587 --> 00:47:04.722 align:middle line:90%
coming in from Robbie.

00:47:04.722 --> 00:47:06.957 align:middle line:84%
After near-death
experience, are people

00:47:06.957 --> 00:47:08.492 align:middle line:90%
more psychic or intuitive?

00:47:08.492 --> 00:47:11.262 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever heard that from
the cases that you've studied?

00:47:11.262 --> 00:47:12.963 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Well,
thank you, Robbie.

00:47:12.963 --> 00:47:13.497 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:47:13.497 --> 00:47:13.631 align:middle line:90%
It's a great question.

00:47:13.631 --> 00:47:15.299 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: And you know,
this is something

00:47:15.299 --> 00:47:17.001 align:middle line:84%
I began to see from
the very beginning.

00:47:17.001 --> 00:47:20.337 align:middle line:84%
I remember a wonderful
woman who was

00:47:20.337 --> 00:47:23.908 align:middle line:84%
the receptionist of a medical
doctor in Macon, Georgia.

00:47:23.908 --> 00:47:25.409 align:middle line:90%
My dad was a doctor there.

00:47:25.409 --> 00:47:29.513 align:middle line:84%
And one of his fellow
physicians, his receptionist

00:47:29.513 --> 00:47:31.382 align:middle line:90%
had had this experience.

00:47:31.382 --> 00:47:34.618 align:middle line:84%
And she talked with me
about this, Mrs. Stokes.

00:47:34.618 --> 00:47:39.523 align:middle line:84%
And what she told me was that,
yes, that after her experience,

00:47:39.523 --> 00:47:41.258 align:middle line:84%
she found, for
example, that when

00:47:41.258 --> 00:47:44.462 align:middle line:84%
she would go into the
elevator with people,

00:47:44.462 --> 00:47:46.697 align:middle line:84%
that she would have
this way of picking up

00:47:46.697 --> 00:47:50.234 align:middle line:84%
on what people were thinking
or what their troubles were,

00:47:50.234 --> 00:47:51.168 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:47:51.168 --> 00:47:54.071 align:middle line:84%
And exactly how to
account for that,

00:47:54.071 --> 00:47:58.109 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, except to say
that this experience really

00:47:58.109 --> 00:48:01.378 align:middle line:84%
does break down
people's ego boundaries.

00:48:01.378 --> 00:48:04.048 align:middle line:84%
It's like they become
different people.

00:48:04.048 --> 00:48:05.816 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
it makes them more

00:48:05.816 --> 00:48:08.152 align:middle line:84%
attuned to the
feeling of others.

00:48:08.152 --> 00:48:10.387 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It breaks down
many different constructs

00:48:10.387 --> 00:48:13.491 align:middle line:84%
of reality, including
fear of death.

00:48:13.491 --> 00:48:14.859 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: Including
fear of death.

00:48:14.859 --> 00:48:19.330 align:middle line:84%
And also including the whole
notion of space and time.

00:48:19.330 --> 00:48:21.398 align:middle line:84%
People say that,
in this experience,

00:48:21.398 --> 00:48:25.569 align:middle line:84%
space and time as you and
I appreciate it now just

00:48:25.569 --> 00:48:26.437 align:middle line:90%
fail to exist.

00:48:26.437 --> 00:48:27.738 align:middle line:90%
They're not a factor anymore.

00:48:27.738 --> 00:48:29.273 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I really
want to mention,

00:48:29.273 --> 00:48:31.609 align:middle line:84%
and I want to make sure that
I'm clear about the fact

00:48:31.609 --> 00:48:34.912 align:middle line:84%
that I don't want to speak about
death being a trivial thing.

00:48:34.912 --> 00:48:38.349 align:middle line:84%
Death is a very
honorable transition.

00:48:38.349 --> 00:48:38.916 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Yes.

00:48:38.916 --> 00:48:41.752 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And people have
many different senses of it.

00:48:41.752 --> 00:48:45.389 align:middle line:84%
It's the number one
fear of Americans.

00:48:45.389 --> 00:48:49.126 align:middle line:84%
It is also a lot
about the unknown.

00:48:49.126 --> 00:48:51.428 align:middle line:84%
And so I want to make
sure people understand

00:48:51.428 --> 00:48:54.398 align:middle line:84%
the conversation we're having
completely, fully honors

00:48:54.398 --> 00:48:55.299 align:middle line:90%
the experience.

00:48:55.299 --> 00:48:55.666 align:middle line:90%
>>MOODY: Oh, yes.

00:48:55.666 --> 00:48:57.501 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And anyone who's
had the experience,

00:48:57.501 --> 00:49:00.271 align:middle line:84%
of a near-death experience
or the loss of a loved one,

00:49:00.271 --> 00:49:02.706 align:middle line:84%
I definitely want to mention
that this is to be honored.

00:49:02.706 --> 00:49:04.141 align:middle line:90%
This is about education.

00:49:04.141 --> 00:49:06.610 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: You know that death
is the ultimate seriousness

00:49:06.610 --> 00:49:07.645 align:middle line:90%
in a way.

00:49:07.645 --> 00:49:10.514 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is not
something to trivialize.

00:49:10.514 --> 00:49:12.249 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No, it
absolutely is not.

00:49:12.249 --> 00:49:15.119 align:middle line:84%
>>MOODY: These are the
worst and most painful

00:49:15.119 --> 00:49:17.388 align:middle line:84%
feelings of all,
are the feelings

00:49:17.388 --> 00:49:18.522 align:middle line:90%
of the loss of a loved one.

00:49:18.522 --> 00:49:21.392 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That people have
tried to explain and heal

00:49:21.392 --> 00:49:24.829 align:middle line:84%
from for thousands and thousands
of years, since-- as you say,

00:49:24.829 --> 00:49:25.930 align:middle line:90%
in antiquity.

00:49:25.930 --> 00:49:29.333 align:middle line:84%
There's a great clip that-- in
the movie "Life After Life,"

00:49:29.333 --> 00:49:31.769 align:middle line:84%
which is a Gaiam
movie, by the way, that

00:49:31.769 --> 00:49:35.472 align:middle line:84%
explains how the fear
of death goes away

00:49:35.472 --> 00:49:38.175 align:middle line:84%
after this experience from these
people that are interviewed.

